Climate is a problem where all can contribute! There are so many ways to throw your hat in the ring and find your way to make a difference. Start today, and then again tomorrow and the day after. Thank you for your effort!
If you have been stuck, every little forward movement is worth celebrating in a small way.

Recognize your process will be uneven. Find people who will support what you are doing and will let you report to them. Share your good days with them and the ones where you lose traction. Plan to start again and again and again.
Be Good to Yourself!

Reduce the crazy and forge ahead despite what's lost. We all need to carry on for the future of our loved ones and for all our fellow animal and plant travelers on this planet who don't have a vote, or say how it unfurls for them.

Just because you can't step from today into that job, don't let that slow you from setting your plan in action. Learning about the entire field to get to the position you want will let you know where the resources are and how the politics are played.

If your desired future position is a very far reach, develop your steps to get there. Ask people doing the work how to get to that level. Find a mentor who can help you understand what's required of you.
You will benefit from the stretch into your future arc! If you are young and starting how here's attitude (https://t.co/GDMORipVVg) to get you moving.

You won't likely start at the top of your next career arc. Look for something worthwhile you can imagine you can do. For challenge you might think of your next assignment, your next job requires about a third new things you don't know how to do.
Future Arc of Your Career
Take the initiative at the beginning of 2023. If you are reading this later, act like this is the beginning of the rest of your life and lean into your resolve and make things happen today!

If you have stopped in your tracks, more waiting is not the answer! Resolve to do something even if it isn't your whole move at once. If you find more time slips by, you may well benefit from some professional help. More waiting is not helping.
No More Waiting
Going beyond arbitrary markers of CO2 has effects, but letting it unfurl even more is so much worse. Don't let those sharp edges, those criteria thresholds, paralyze your efforts!

There are many scary terms thrown about that suggest once we cross that threshold, all is lost. That's BS! Every tenth of degree we hold down the temperature is worthwhile! Every species of animal and plant we save is huge!
Criteria Reality
Wasting more time on dead end jobs, no matter how much they pay is a waste of the future.

If you need help with guidance on what to choose that is worth doing, use All We Can Save  and Project Drawdown (https://t.co/SdvKL8hkm7) for great ideas and summaries. We can work on the most important things to leverage the best outcome.
You should find the most important work needed to save the best of this earth. It is magnificent and it is worth the effort!

I was impressed by the book, All We Can Save (https://t.co/I2Btuf4Z9T). The articles in the book focus on what is needed next to make our world the best we can. Now is the time to start your work, our work on all we can work on.
All We Can Work on
Research and find positive coworkers who are making progress on the problem(s) you think worth working on. Then look at the resources they have to work with.

Trying to turn the work environment and attitudes around AND make positive headway against climate issues is too much. That negative attitude will limit your ability to make the most of your resources.
If these associates are part of your work environment and you make no progress with them quickly, start looking for a new venue, a new job (https://t.co/4JFxlcCZmG).
Guide them to use their resource to aid in the solution. Learn to lead towards success.

If your associates are bringing you down, set limits on the time you spend with them. No matter who they are. In some way, they are your enemy when they are in that mode. Prepare for interaction with them by limiting the topics you discuss. Share the problem you are working on.
Limiting Associations
We should learn from the past, but being emotionally paralyzed only brings more loss.

What's lost is significant already and we will lose more before this even begins to slow down. Making that your catastrophe does not help. What we need is to mobilize for the future and cut our attachment to the losses. Each day has to be faced with it's new problems.
Re-framing the past
Paralysis doesn't work, mistakes do more than nothing as you learn from them.

Ask people in the field what they are using for self education. Start your own educational projects to learn more. Ask people about positions where people are working on the problem you selected. Start applying for full time positions. Do something even if it might be wrong.

Take up an internship or volunteer position if you don't find you are ready for full employment. Ask for increase responsibility and demonstrate initiative. Make contacts with people who you admire doing the work. Ask to be included in their projects.
Break down your process into steps you can manage. Find part of the climate problem you can work on. Locate people who are doing the work. Go talk to those people about starting in the field.
The rest of us need to identify where our contributions will be part of the solution. In large numbers we have the ability to bring great force to bear on the climate issues.

First, recognize that you don't have to save the world. That's not going to happen. Few people in this world are able to manipulate enough major resource to have a major impact on climate change even at a local level. Those are not who I am addressing here.
Surgical parsing
Some specialize in addressing issues related to climate and environmental concerns.

Start working to overcome this and get professional help if this has gone on for any length of time. You will find professional mental health under the titles of psychologist, psychiatrist, and clinical social worker in your local area.

If this has become a mental health issue, depression, anxiety or both, you can benefit from psychotherapy to get beyond this. Certainly letting your fear of the future, or remorse for what could have been, stop you from adding your contribution to the effort is unfortunate.
Some active surgery on your worries about the climate crisis might be necessary to get past your paralysis, or maybe it's just plain procrastination. It doesn't matter, inaction serves you not.
If the climate is causing craziness for you, let's take steps to reduce the crazy and forge ahead. Paralysis may come from being overwhelmed by the magnitude of the climate problem.
